rComments: He is a great prof. He not only is great at teaching, but also is really caring. I think he is the only prof that I have ever met that actually post the final's answer so that we could check where we went wrong, which would also benefit future students.

One of my favourite profs of 3rd year ECE! He's great at teaching probability and always makes sure to clear up common misconceptions, which I really like. He got me really interested in the subject. If you listen in class & do the weekly practice problems from the textbook you'll be good for the tests.

Professor Liang is very proficient at teaching probability related courses. Following his classes requires you to pay attention but he will always clearly explain his ideas; I always ended up with great marks in his classes. Very friendly professor who is always willing to give students course or work related advice!
Extremely caring professor, a knowledgeable man and a wonderful person. He makes me want to study probability during the toughest of times.
